******
[2]
Date: Wed 24 Oct 2018
Source: Investor (Bulgaria) [in Bulgarian, machine trans., edited]
https://www.investor.bg/ikonomika-i-politika/332/a/predprieti-sa-merki-sreshtu-afrikanskata-chuma-po-svinete-v-silistrensko-270637/


A total of 20 km [approx. 12 mi] of a crisis and another 20 km [approx. 12 mi] of buffer zone are formed around the Kaynardzha village, where a body of a wild boar was found in the vicinity of the Bulgarian-Romanian border a few days ago, BNT reported. Samples are positive for African swine fever, according to information from the Bulgarian Food Safety Agency (BSAF).

At a meeting of the Epizootic Commission in Silistra today [Wed 24 Oct 2018], the measures for the prevention of the disease in domestic pigs, on the private farms and in the industrial, commercial enterprises have been discussed. The lists of the private farms are to be updated.

[Byline: Nadezhda Bocheva]

