Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Bulgaria has submitted on Tue 23 Oct 2018, an official immediate notification to the OIE about the above, its 1st ASF case in a wild boar. See at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=28379.

The current case, a wild boar, is located in the village Kaynardzha, bordering Romania's Calarasi province. Kaynardzha is located about 22 km [approx. 23 mi] south-east to the Bulgarian port city Silistra on the southern bank of the lower Danube river (map at https://tinyurl.com/ycmqaew7). From Silistra westwards, the Danube divides the 2 countries, forming a natural boundary between Romania and Bulgaria; Silistra is the western end of the fence planned to stretch from the Black Sea coast in north-east Bulgaria.

The 1st (and, so far, only) ASF outbreak in Bulgaria's domestic pigs was notified early September 2018 (20180903.6005066) involving backyard pigs on a farm in the village Tutrakantsi, Provadia, province of Varna (map at https://tinyurl.com/yaydognk).

Additional information on Bulgaria's ASF prevention policy, including a map presenting the fence route, is available in Bulgaria's SC PAFF presentation of 17 Oct 2018, at https://ec.europa.eu/food/sites/food/files/animals/docs/reg-com_ahw_20181017_pres_asf_bul.pdf. The presentation preceded the current wild-boar case. It would be interesting to obtain information on the structure of the (completed?) erected fence. Wild boars are known as notorious fence trespassers; it would require a robust fence to keep them away.

Romania has notified the OIE on 18 Oct 2018 about an outbreak in domestic pigs, in the southern province Teleorman, facing Bulgaria's Pleven province. Given start date was 28 Sep 2018 (see 20181018.6098967). Map at https://tinyurl.com/ybpshdsy; this presents a considerable leap westwards from Romania's south-eastern explosive ASF cluster.

Additional (17) outbreaks in southern Romania, adjacent to the Bulgarian border, affecting domestic pigs and wild boar, have been reported in today's (24 Oct 2018) follow-up report No 11, with map; http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=28314. - Mod.AS

HealthMap/ProMED map available at:
Silistra, Silistra, Bulgaria: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6110151,42108]
